reviewText: It's a bit inconceivable to think about a junk food angel, but hey, it was just a movie. I really liked the wise talking, truffle loving Angel of Death whose work ethic left a little to be desired.  This is not an earth shaking movie, but it may cause some people to stop and think about their past - and more importantly their future.
This is a really cute film with a powerful message. I think folks from 9 to 90 will enjoy this film.
